      <!-- Technical Implementation -->
      <section class="section" data-section="implementation">
        <div class="section-content">
          <span class="section-number">07 — Implementation</span>
          <h2 class="section-title">Making It Fast</h2>
          <div class="section-text">
            <p>
              A naive implementation checks every boid against every other boid,
              resulting in quadratic time complexity. With just 1,000 boids,
              that's one million distance calculations per time step. As the
              number of boids grows, this quickly becomes intractable.
            </p>
            <p>
              The solution? A <strong>spatial hash grid</strong>. By dividing
              space into cells, each boid only needs to check neighbors in
              nearby cells. This reduces complexity dramatically, allowing
              thousands of boids to flock smoothly at 60fps.
            </p>
          </div>
          <!-- <Prism class="code-block" lang="ts" code={CODE_SPATIAL_HASH} /> -->
